<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-636] Revise internal data structures of ThreadSafeClientConnManager</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-636</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>ThreadSafeClientConnManager internal data structures can be improved:&lt;br/&gt;
- keep track of issued connections with weak references&lt;br/&gt;
- use class derived from WeakReference instead of a lookup table for callbacks from ReferenceThread&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;(or drop ReferenceThread in favor of occasionally polling the issued connections for leaks)&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
